Releases are tagged by API major and minor version.

Buils instructions:

  $ mkdir build
  $ cd build
  $ cmake â€“D__ARCH:STRING=intel64 ../
  $ make

Replace intel64 with ia32 as appropriate.

Similar repositories can be found here:

https://github.com/Rodeo314/libmfx
https://github.com/lu-zero/mfx_dispatch

The hardware-accelerated libraries can be installed using the Intel Media Server Studio:

https://software.intel.com/en-us/intel-media-server-studio

The API 1.19 release was extracted from the 2017 release, in intel-linux-media_generic_16.5-55964_64bit.tar.gz.

Troubleshooting and further info:

http://streambuilder.pro/docs/requirements/enabling-iqsv/
https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/harnessing-handbrake
https://trac.ffmpeg.org/wiki/HWAccelIntro
